<paragraph id="8BB636D2FFDBFFDAFD26FD40E255FCC1" blockId="30.[749,1338,759,1178]" pageId="30" pageNumber="437">
Taxonomy. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D51FFDBFFDAFC6BFD40E50FFCC1" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Mammalia" family="Cervidae" genus="Cervus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="30" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bezoarcticus">Cervus bezoarcticus Linnaeus, 1758</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B613C8FFFDBFFDAFC89FCACE255FCC1" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3785196337" box="[834,1128,795,824]" pageId="30" pageNumber="437">
Pernanbuco (
<collectingCountry id="F31E7642FFDBFFDAFBC8FCACE266FCC1" box="[1027,1115,795,824]" name="Brazil" pageId="30" pageNumber="437">Brazil</collectingCountry>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB636D2FFDBFFDAFD26FC89E315FC2D" blockId="30.[749,1338,759,1178]" pageId="30" pageNumber="437">The scientific name of the species originates from bezoar stone, a calcareous mass allegedly found in the stomachs of this deer. Five subspecies are recognized.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
